## Superseded standard pin (T5.3, 2026-05-18)

This archive shipped the FSM frontend Phase B SDK instrumentation
against Workiva `opentelemetry: ^0.18.0` (`examples/forge-fsm-example/frontend/`).
The 5 Dart files in `lib/core/telemetry/` :

- `telemetry_setup.dart`
- `error_reporter.dart`
- `interceptors/tracing_interceptor.dart`
- `observers/tracing_bloc_observer.dart`
- `observers/tracing_navigation_observer.dart`

…have been **rewritten on the Dartastic ecosystem** in T5.3
(`t5-otel-dartastic-realign`, archived 2026-05-18) :

- `dartastic_opentelemetry: ^1.1.0-beta.6`
- `flutterrific_opentelemetry: ^0.4.0`

Substitution motivation : Q-006 — Workiva `opentelemetry 0.18.11` is
**web-only** on pub.dev (`Platforms: Web`). The consuming archetype
(`full-stack-monorepo` frontend Flutter, mobile + web) requires
Android + iOS support. Q-006 surfaced 2026-05-16 via
`cli-trust-harness` Option B validation.

See `.forge/standards/flutter/opentelemetry.md` v2.0.0 § Migration
from v1.1.0 for the symbol-by-symbol from→to table, and
`.forge/changes/t5-otel-dartastic-realign/` for the full change.

**Article V immutability** : this `.forge-update-notes` file is the
ONLY addition to this archived change since its archive date. All
other files remain byte-identical.

**Pattern** : ADR-T53-003 — per-archive `.forge-update-notes`
(Option A) + global supersession graph via
`.forge/changes/t5-otel-dartastic-realign/.forge.yaml::depends_on`
(Option C).
